title: piat
body: PIAT or Projector, Infantry, Anti Tank was a British anti-tank weapon developed during WW2 that was used by British, Commonwealth, and other allied forces during it and saw limited use afterwards during the First Indochina War and the Korean War. Unlike German Panzerschreck or American Bazooka PIAT wasn't a rocket launcher but rather a spigot mortar system which had both its own advantages (no back-blast, capable of indirect fire) and disadvantages (heavy recoil, harder to operate).

It was created by Steven Moffat and Mark Gatiss, and stars Benedict Cumberbatch as [[Sherlock Holmes]] and Martin Freeman as [[john_hamish_watson|Doctor John Watson]]. After an unbroadcast pilot in 2009, the first series of three 90-minute episodes was transmitted on [[BBC (broadcaster)|]] One and BBC HD in July and August 2010, with a second series of three episodes first broadcast in January 2012. title: arachnid_(series)
body:
A 2009 manga written by [[Murata Shinya]], illustrated by [[Ifuji Shinsen]], and serialized on Gangan Joker. It follows the adventures of [[Fujii Alice]], a girl who is trained to use a concentration disorder to her advantage as a spider-themed assassin. It's notable for battle narrations that compare the characters' abilities to the behavior of insects, sometimes to a rather nonsensical effect.

It has a spinoff storyline named Caterpillar which serves as a prequel and features a woman named Imomushi, who is a member of the assassin organization that will later target Alice.

title: effects_pedal
body:
A foot-operated device, typically used by players of [[electric guitar]] (but in fact usable by any musical [[instrument]] or device with an audio output), plugged into the signal path between the instrument and the [[amplifier]] in order to alter the properties of emanating sound.

Single effects pedals can be of various types including chorus, reverb, overdrive, distortion, wah-wah, pitch-shift and so on. It is common to see several effects pedals linked in series on a live stage, often grouped onto a [[pedal board]], where they can be toggled in any combination. Multi-effects pedals combine many of these together into the same box.

title: f90y_cluster_gundam
body:
A [[mobile suit]] from [[Gundam Silhouette Formula 91]].

A radical departure from the previous [[F90 Gundam]] units, the Cluster Gundam incorporated a Core Block System that functioned as its cockpit and backpack, so the pilot’s rate of survival is greatly increased. Following the trend of equipping different Mission Packs for various roles, the Cluster is fitted with several hardpoints for attaching a wide variety of equipment. It also features a large number of beam weapons, including the mega beam bazooka, which was recently formally adopted by the Federation army and highly regarded by regular pilots. 

One known pilot of the Cluster Gundam is [[Wolf Lyle]].

title: uruguay
body: A country in South America. It shares borders with [[Argentina]] to its west and southwest and [[Brazil]] to its north and northeast. The Uruguay national football team has won the FIFA World Cup on two occasions. Uruguay won the inaugural tournament on home soil in 1930 (First World Cup) and again in 1950.

title: paraguay
body: A country in South America. It is bordered by [[Argentina]] to the south and southwest, [[Brazil]] to the east and northeast, and Bolivia to the northwest. Although one of only two landlocked countries in South America (the other being Bolivia), the country has coasts, beaches and ports on the Paraguay and Paraná rivers that give exit to the Atlantic Ocean through the Paraná-Paraguay Waterway. More than 90% of the population speak various dialects of the Guarani language alongside Spanish.

title: ecuador
body: A country in northwestern South America, bordered by [[Colombia]] on the north, [[Peru]] on the east and south, and the Pacific Ocean on the west. Ecuador also includes the Galápagos Islands in the Pacific, about 1,000 kilometers (621 mi) west of the mainland. The capital is Quito.

title: venezuela
body: A country on the northern coast of South America. It has the world's largest known oil reserves and has been one of the world's leading exporters of oil, but oil quickly came to dominate exports and government revenues. The excesses and poor policies of the incumbent government led to the collapse of Venezuela's entire economy.

title: colombia
body: A country in South America. It's rich cultural heritage reflects influences by various Amerindian civilizations, European settlement, African slaves, and immigration from Europe and the Middle East. Spanish is the nation's official language, besides which over 70 languages are spoken.

title: costa_rica
body: A country in Central America. It is known for its long-standing and stable democracy, and for its highly educated workforce, most of whom speak English. Following the brief Costa Rican Civil War in 1948, it permanently abolished its army in 1949, becoming one of only a few sovereign nations without a standing army.

title: nicaragua

title: gray_whale
body:
The [b]gray whale[/b] (Eschrichtius robustus) is a baleen whale that migrates between feeding and breeding grounds yearly. It reaches a length of 14.9 meters (49 ft), a weight of up to 41 tonnes (90,000 lb) and lives between 55 and 70 years.
The common name of the whale comes from the gray patches and white mottling on its dark skin.
Sometimes confused with the [[humpback whale]], but gray whales have shorter mouths and do not have a white underbelly.

title: humpback_whale
body:
The humpback [[whale]] (Megaptera novaeangliae) is a species of baleen whale. It is one of the larger rorqual (a section of baleen whales) species, with adults ranging in length from 12–16 m (39–52 ft) and weighing around 25–30 t (28–33 short tons). 
The humpback has a distinctive body shape, with long pectoral fins and a knobbly head. 
It is known for breaching and other distinctive surface behaviors.

title: golden_axe

[b]Golden Axe[/b] (ゴールデンアックス [i]Goruden Arzu[/i]) is a side-scrolling, beat 'em up, hack and slash arcade [[video game]] released in 1989 by [[SEGA]] for the System 16-B arcade hardware. It is the first game in the Golden Axe series.

"Uchida Makoto":http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Makoto_Uchida was the primary developer of the game and also was responsible for the creation of [[Juuouki|Altered Beast]] a year before. title: olivia_(kureiji_ollie)
body:
[[Kureiji Ollie]]'s human counterpart from a parallel universe. Olivia is fully human with no signs of zombification, with mostly long red hair and red eyes, and is well-dressed. In contrast to Ollie, Olivia is demure and soft-spoken, prefers peaceful endeavors, and is afraid of violence.

Oddly enough, whenever Ollie "summons" Olivia to play the game for her, Olivia will usually manage to get something that Ollie actually wants (such as getting a legendary item from [[Apex Legends]]'s loot boxes), which leads into Ollie instantly "sending her back" out of jealousy.

She's essentially an alter-ego created to demonstrate Ollie's voice acting skill, similar to [[Kurokami Fubuki]].

title: charles_(masterwork_apocalypse)
body:
Character from [[Masterwork Apocalypse]].

[b]Origin:[/b] Natural Selection, a manuscript written by Charles Darwin, in which he presented his theory of natural selection and its role in biological evolution. He did not publish the work while he was alive, but wrote an abstract, titled On the Origin of Species by Means of Natural Selection. title: plum_blossom_(masterwork_apocalypse)
body:
Character from [[Masterwork Apocalypse]].

[b]Origin:[/b] 梅花易数 (rough English translation: Plum Blossoms are Easy to Count), a book based on mathematics in yili xue (義理學, "principle study") combined with "xiangshu xue (象數學, "image-number study"), being one of ancient Chinese divination methods. title: vignette
body:
Vignette refers exclusively to small diorama-style illustrations and pixel art in pixiv. As a feature, there is a composition that looks like a three-dimensional cutout of a part of the scene.

It's kind of lonely if it's just a character, I'm not good at the background, but I want to draw a little, I enjoy delusionally making it three-dimensional, it's small and fashionable, I love vignettes! There may be various reasons such as ..., but most of the time, the things that the person wants to draw are condensed, so there are many illustrations that are spectacular even with small particles. On the other hand, the sense of putting together a large number of items clearly appears, so it may be a good idea to consider it as the subject of the study.
Pixel art that depicts a vignette is especially called a "dot vignette".

The original meaning is a word derived from the French word vigne (grape), which originally meant the ivy pattern of grapes. After that, it has a meaning as a decorative term, which refers to all "decorative patterns" with arabesque and other plant motifs. Then, meanings such as "illustration (as a decoration of a book)", "portrait with a blurred background", and "small thing" were added, and in turn, a small diorama came to be called a vignette.

Source: https://dic.pixiv.net/a/%E3%83%B4%E3%82%A3%E3%83%8D%E3%83%83%E3%83%88

title: g3_battlecruiser
body: A post-World War 1 British battlecruiser project, 4 ships of this class were ordered but none were apparently laid down before the project was cancelled due to Washington Naval Treaty, materials and ideas meant for this class (alongside with those meant for their battleship counterparts: N3-class) were ultimately used in design and construction of Nelson-class battleships. Even though G3s were officially classified as battlecruisers in design they were closer to what we would today consider fast battleships; featuring main battery of 9 406mm guns mounted in three triple turrets, 16 155mm secondary guns in 8 twin turrets, 356mm (magazines) to 305mm (machinery spaces) thick armored belt, 203mm to 73mm thick armored deck (areas around magazines being once again significantly more heavily armored than those around machinery spaces), heavily armored turrets  (444mm thick faces, 330mm to 229mm sides, 203mm roof), and armored bulkheads 305mm to 254mm thick, with design speed of 32 knots and full displacement of 54k tons. G3's most notable feature (and the one which allowed to it to as heavily armored as it was) was its rather unorthodox turret placement; 2 turrets (A and B) forward with B turret superfiring over A turret, one turret midship (X), this layout allowed the armor to be concentrated in much smaller area than it would had been possible if a more conventional turret layout had been used. For more info about G3s and their design history both "Wikipedia":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/G3_battlecruiser and "Warship Projects":https://warshipprojects.com/2017/09/27/washington-cherry-trees-ii-part-3/ have decent articles about them.

title: hms_howe_(battleship)
body: A British King George V-class battleship, laid down in 1937, launched in 1940, commissioned into service in 1942, put in reserve status in 1951 and sold for scrapping in 1957. Took part in Operation Husky (Allied Invasion of Sicily), Operation Avalanche (part of Allied invasion of Italy), helped to escort surrendered Italian battleships Italia and Vittorio Veneto to Alexandria before undergoing a refit and being sent to east where she was involved in fight against Japanese first as part of the British Eastern Fleet and then as a member of the British Pacific Fleet.

title: watashi_(jintai)
body:
The narrator and main character of [[Jinrui wa Suitai Shimashita]]. Her name is unknown; she is referred to as "Watashi" by convention. 

She is tall, generally has [[very long hair]], and is often seen in long [[dress]]es. Other aspects of her appearance are inconsistent, even in official art. 

In the original novel illustrations by [[Yamazaki Tooru]], both her hair and eyes are a pinkish brown in color, and she has distinctive 'stringy' hair. In later novel illustrations by [[Tobe Sunaho]], she's drawn with [[blonde hair]] and [[green eyes]]. In the anime, her character design resembles Tobe's illustrations, but her hair is [[pink hair|pink]]. It's also mentioned in the anime that she has somewhat [[large breasts]].

title: midler
body:
Midler is the user of the shapeshifting Stand [[High Priestess (stand)|]], which has hard teeth which it can use to crush things easily. Initially, the wielder of the Stand was unknown, High Priestess being soundly defeated by Jotaro in [[Stardust Crusaders]], leaving only an unconscious body for the Crusaders to find afterward.

Her current design and name (a nod to singer Bette Midler) first appeared in the CPS-3 game of the series produced by CAPCOM. Upon being asked, Hirohiko Araki created her character to complement the game's roster at that time.

She has enjoyed a degree of popularity since her introduction.
